FOR
5 HOUSE BILL NO. 1746 By: Lawson and Moore
6
7
8 COMMITTEE SUBSTITUTE
9 An Act relating to children; defining terms;
authorizing a facility to prepare and transmit a
10 safety plan to the Office of Juvenile Affairs when
certain determination is made; providing what shall
11 be included in a safety plan; directing the Office to
approve or deny the safety plan within certain time
12 period; providing when time period begins;
authorizing a facility to transmit a safety plan at
13 any time; providing methods by which a safety plan
may be transmitted; directing the facility to retain
14 proof of transmission; providing that the safety plan
shall be deemed approved if the Office does not
15 provide written approval or denial within certain
time period; requiring a denial to state specific
16 reasons for denial; providing that nothing shall be
construed to authorize certain isolation or reduced
17 access to services; directing the facility to
maintain the safety plan and supporting
18 documentation; providing for codification; and
providing an effective date.
19
20
21
22 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
23
